Trie Node Structure

Each node stores:

children
endOfWord flag


class TrieNode{
    TrieNode[] children;
    boolean endOfWord;
    public TrieNode(){
        children = new TrieNode[26];
        endOfWord = false;
    }
}

Why 26?

a-z

Index:

a -> 0
b -> 1
c -> 2
...
z -> 25

Formula:

int index = ch - 'a';

Example:

'c' - 'a'
= 2